
Atlanta Hawks center Jason Collier was scheduled to give the team's formal greeting to fans before a scrimmage at Woodward Academy Saturday afternoon. It never happened. Collier, 28, died early Saturday after having trouble breathing while sleeping. An autopsy was performed Saturday afternoon to determine the cause of death. Collier's wife, Katie, called his parents in Springfield, Ohio at 3:20 a.m. Saturday after calling an ambulance to their home on Lake Lanier. 

